---
title: Testing bananas
---

BTeX can handle formulas like \(x^2 + 1\),
\[\int f(x) \mathop{\mathrm{d}\mu}.\]
We have \code{cd} diagrams too:
\[\begin{cd}
A \ar[r] & B \ar[d]\\
C & D \ar[l, dashed]
\end{cd}\]
Ti\emph{k}Z is also supported:
\[\begin{tikzcd}
A \arrow[rd] \arrow[r, "\phi"] & B \\
& C
\end{tikzcd}\]

